{% block content %}
  {{ page_header({ h1: 'Add a groundhog', backUrl: '/', backText: 'Home' }) }}

  <div class="max-width--850">
    
    <p>{{ site_title({ url: true }) }} aspires to be (and maybe already is) the leading source for prognosticating groundhogs and their yearly predictions. As such, the door is very much open to adding talented, up-and-coming groundhogs to our roster of classic, mainstream groundhogs.</p>
    <p>It is also possible to <a href="#editing-a-groundhog">update/amend data for existing groundhogs</a>.</p>

    <h2 class="h3">Before adding a groundhog</h2>
    <p>Your groundhog must have a public web presence (a Twitter account or Facebook page is okay) and a record of predictions going back at least <strong>3</strong> years. (2 if you ask nicely.)</p>

    <h2 class="h3">Submitting a new groundhog</h2>
    <p>You will need 3 things to add a new groundhog:</p>
    <ol class="with-decimals">
        <li><a href="#submitting-a-groundhog--basic-information">Basic information</a> about your groundhog</li>
        <li><a href="#submitting-a-groundhog--predictions">A list of predictions</a> by year</li>
        <li><a href="#submitting-a-groundhog--photo">A photo</a></li>
    </ol>
    <p><a href="https://forms.gle/fki9UL1kwjSusbL59" target="_blank">Here is a Google Form you can use to submit a new groundhog</a>. It should take you about 5 minutes.</p>

    <h3 class="h5" id="submitting-a-groundhog--basic-information">1. Basic information</h3>
    <p>All groundhogs consist of the following:</p>
    <ul class="with-bullets">
      <li>Name</li>
      <li>Location</li>
      <li>Website (and direct link to latest prediction)</li>
      <li>A description, preferably 40-70 words</li>
      <li>Type of animal (if not a literal groundhog)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="h5" id="submitting-a-groundhog--predictions">2. A list of predictions</h3>
    <p>An Excel/CSV/Google Sheets file with 3 columns: <code>year</code>, <code>shadow</code>, and <code>details</code>. </p>
    <p>For example:</p>
    <ul class="with-bullets">
      <li><a href="https://www.groundhog.org/Files/Admin/history/UpdatedGroundhog%5FDay%5FPredictions%2Epdf" target="_blank">Punxatawney Phil’s historical predictions</a>, which inspired my format.</li>
      <li><a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1RX0CBSbTXj6LQK0zXpoPay_hjG44mW1wwFGYsj9G82E/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">The spreadsheet I created for Punxatawney Phil</a> in Google Sheets</a>, including “details”</li>
      <li><a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1jQIG4PY-RwiVm2GhsrpZ_EQZyjhLgaPPhiDWap8qUhE/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">The spreadsheet I created for Buckeye Chuck</a> in Google Sheets</a>, with no added “details”</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You can make a copy of <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1LKl_eyr90sPJzNoDL-YMpKReEjS4lGvsppAbrRwCFTY/edit?usp=sharing" target="_blank">this empty Google Sheets template</a> to fill out on your own.</p>
    
    <h3 class="h5" id="submitting-a-groundhog--photo">3. A photo</h3>
    <p>There are no hard and fast rules here, but try to find a photo that is mostly the groundhog and no people. Most photos so far use landscape orientation but that’s not mandatory.</p>

    <h2 class="h3" id="editing-a-groundhog">Editing a groundhog</h2>
    <p class="mb--0">I have tried to make sure that all data on the site is accurate but mistakes do happen. If you noticed any information that is incorrect or incomplete (eg, to add extra predictions, edit a groundhog’s description, add a new photo), please email me at <a class="underline" href="mailto:paul@pcraig3.ca">paul@pcraig3.ca</a> and I can do it in a day or two.</p>
  </div>
{% endblock %}
